.nh
.TH clnku 1 "clnku" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
clnku \- a minimal coding agent (plain CLI)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBclnku\fP [\fB-p\fP \fItask\fP] [\fB--model\fP \fIname\fP] [\fB--base-url\fP \fIurl\fP] [\fB--max-steps\fP \fIn\fP] [\fB--full-send\fP] [\fB--load-messages\fP \fIfile\fP] [\fB--event-log\fP \fIfile\fP] [\fB--trajectory\fP \fIfile\fP] [\fB-v\fP|\fB--verbose\fP] [\fB--version\fP]


.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBclnku\fP is a minimal coding agent that queries LLMs and executes bash commands using a structured JSON turn protocol. It supports both Anthropic and OpenAI-compatible APIs.

.PP
In default mode, \fBclnku\fP starts an interactive REPL. With \fB-p\fP, it runs a single task and exits.

.PP
\fBclnku\fP is the plain CLI variant of the clnkr project, with no external dependencies beyond the Go standard library. A TUI variant is available as \fBclnkr\fP(1).

.PP
The agent communicates through JSON turns: \fBact\fP (execute a command), \fBclarify\fP (ask the user), and \fBdone\fP (signal completion).

.PP
By default, \fBclnku\fP asks for approval before each \fBact\fP turn. Pass \fB--full-send\fP to execute commands immediately without approval.

.PP
Project-specific instructions are loaded from an \fBAGENTS.md\fP file in the current working directory, if present.


.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-p\fP, \fB--prompt\fP \fItask\fP
Run the given task and exit. Without this flag, clnku starts in conversational REPL mode.

.TP
\fB--model\fP \fIname\fP
LLM model identifier (default: claude-sonnet-4-20250514).

.TP
\fB--base-url\fP \fIurl\fP
LLM API endpoint (default: https://api.anthropic.com). If the URL contains "anthropic.com", the Anthropic adapter is used; otherwise, the OpenAI-compatible adapter is used.

.TP
\fB--max-steps\fP \fIn\fP
Maximum agent iterations. 0 uses the default of 100.

.TP
\fB--full-send\fP
Execute every \fBact\fP turn immediately. Without this flag, clnku asks for approval before each command.

.TP
\fB--load-messages\fP \fIfile\fP
Read a JSON array of messages from \fIfile\fP and prepend them to the conversation before starting. The format matches \fB--trajectory\fP output, so one agent's trajectory can seed another agent's context. Host-generated JSON \fB[state]\fR messages in that transcript restore the current working directory.

.TP
\fB--event-log\fP \fIfile\fP
Write every agent event as a JSONL line to \fIfile\fP\&. Each line is a JSON object with "type" and "payload" fields. Uses O_APPEND for atomic writes, safe to tail from another process.

.TP
\fB--trajectory\fP \fIfile\fP
After the task finishes, write the full message history as pretty-printed JSON to \fIfile\fP\&. Written before exit, even on error. Only applies to single-task mode (\fB-p\fP), not the REPL.

.TP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP
Show internal decisions (queries, parsing, working directory).

.TP
\fB--version\fP
Print version and exit.

.TP
\fB--continue\fP
Resume the most recent session for the current project directory. Saved JSON \fB[state]\fR messages restore the last persisted working directory.

.TP
\fB--list-sessions\fP
List all saved sessions for the current project directory.


.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBCLNKR_API_KEY\fP
API key for the LLM provider (required).

.TP
\fBANTHROPIC_API_KEY\fP
Fallback API key when using the Anthropic endpoint.


.SH FILES
.TP
\fBAGENTS.md\fP
If present in the current directory, its contents are appended to the system prompt as project-specific instructions.


.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fP
Success.

.TP
\fB1\fP
Error (no API key, step limit reached, etc.).


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBclnkr\fP(1)


